## 🎓 HSLU Research & Academic Projects

**How can academic projects become the starting point for future research?**

This section presents research projects, presentations, and academic investigations developed throughout my studies in Environmental and Energy Systems Engineering at the Lucerne University of Applied Sciences and Arts (HSLU).

These projects explore a range of topics related to sustainability, environmental systems, energy, climate adaptation, ecological engineering, and emerging technologies. While developed within an academic setting, many of these investigations have contributed to shaping my broader research interests in biomimicry, regenerative systems, nature-based solutions, and future sustainable technologies.

Through coursework, interdisciplinary projects, technical analyses, and scientific communication, these experiences have provided opportunities to explore real-world environmental challenges while developing both engineering and research skills.

### Topics explored:

* Sustainability & Environmental Systems
* Climate Adaptation
* Nature-Based Solutions
* Energy Systems
* Environmental Engineering
* Ecological Thinking
* Emerging Technologies
* Scientific Communication
* Systems Thinking
* Sustainable Innovation

